---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Student Experience | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="What it is like to study with Brenkley Doctoral College — online learning, supervisor matching, peer community, pastoral support, and a lifelong alumni network.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Life at Brenkley Doctoral College</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">The Doctoral Experience</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">A doctorate is a long journey. We are committed to making that journey intellectually stimulating, practically manageable, and deeply supported. Here is what you can expect as a Brenkley Doctoral College researcher.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Online Platform -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Learning Environment</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Your Online Learning Platform</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Brenkley Doctoral College operates through a purpose-built online learning environment designed for doctoral-level study. The platform integrates structured learning pathways, direct supervisor communication, submission management, and access to research resources — all in one place.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Our platform is built around the realities of part-time study. There are no fixed lecture times. Materials are available 24/7, live sessions are recorded, and your academic timeline is tracked and visible to both you and your supervisor at all times.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">The platform connects directly to major academic databases, including access to thousands of peer-reviewed journals relevant to your research area. Brenkley Doctoral College provides full library access as part of your programme fee — there are no additional database subscriptions to purchase.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Academic Library Access</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Full access to EBSCO, JSTOR, Emerald Insight, Sage Journals, and Taylor & Francis collections, included in your programme fee.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Structured Learning Pathways</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Year-by-year learning frameworks guide you through research design, methods training, ethics, writing, and submission preparation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Live Sessions, Always Recorded</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">All live webinars, workshops, and supervision group sessions are recorded and available in your archive within 24 hours.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Progress Dashboard</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">A clear visual tracker shows your progress against milestones, upcoming deadlines, and supervisory meeting log — always up to date.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Supervisor Matching -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Supervision</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Supervisor Matching</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">The supervisory relationship is at the heart of doctoral education. At Brenkley Doctoral College, we take supervisor matching seriously — it is not an administrative afterthought. Before you enrol, the Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise leads a careful process to identify the supervisor whose expertise, methods background, and working style is the best fit for your research.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Expert Matching</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Your supervisor is selected based on alignment between their research expertise and your proposed topic, ensuring intellectually rich supervision from day one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Primary and Second Supervisor</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Every researcher has both a primary supervisor and a second supervisor. The second supervisor provides methodological support and continuity if your primary supervisor is unavailable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Regular Meetings</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">You have a guaranteed minimum of eight supervisor meetings per year, typically fortnightly or monthly depending on your stage. All meetings are logged and minuted on the platform.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Group Supervision</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">In addition to individual meetings, each supervisor group holds quarterly peer sessions. These are invaluable for developing your voice, giving and receiving feedback, and building peer relationships.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Supervision Contract</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">At the start of your programme, you and your supervisors co-create a supervision contract setting out expectations, communication norms, and meeting frequency. This document is revisited at each annual review.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Change Process</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">If a supervisory relationship is not working, Brenkley Doctoral College has a clear, confidential process for reviewing and if necessary changing supervision arrangements. Researcher welfare always comes first.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Peer Community -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Community</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Peer Community</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Doctoral research can be isolating. At Brenkley Doctoral College, we actively counter that by building a genuine community of peer researchers who support, challenge, and inspire each other throughout the journey.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Your cohort — the group of researchers who started in the same intake period as you — forms the core of your peer community. You will share an orientation programme, methods training cohort sessions, and ongoing peer learning circles throughout your studies.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Beyond your cohort, you have access to the wider Brenkley Doctoral College researcher forum, where over 100 active researchers share resources, ask questions, and offer support across all stages of doctoral study.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Cohort Learning Circles</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Monthly peer-led discussion sessions focused on shared challenges — from literature reviews to ethics applications to the experience of writing up.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Writing Retreats</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Online and in-person concentrated writing days, facilitated but unstructured. Researchers come together to write, share a brief update, and stay accountable to their goals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Annual Symposium</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Our annual gathering of the entire Brenkley Doctoral College research community — researchers, supervisors, and alumni — for presentations, workshops, and connection. See the <a href="/symposium" class="text-accent underline">Symposium page</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pastoral Support -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Welfare</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Pastoral Support</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">Doctoral study, alongside a professional career, is demanding. We know that, and we take our duty of care seriously. Brenkley Doctoral College's pastoral framework is led by Dr. Liz Blower, Academic Lead for Operations &amp; Finance, and is designed to support researchers at every stage.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Annual Pastoral Review</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Once per year, every researcher has a dedicated meeting with the Academic Lead for Operations &amp; Finance to discuss wellbeing, progress, and anything that may be affecting their studies — separate from academic supervision.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Open-Door Policy</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Researchers can contact Dr. Liz Blower or the Student Experience team at any time if they are experiencing difficulties. We aim to respond to all welfare-related contacts within one working day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Interruption of Studies</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Life happens. Brenkley Doctoral College has a straightforward process for interrupting studies for health, professional, or personal reasons, without financial penalty during approved interruption periods.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">External Referral</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Where researchers need support beyond academic pastoral care, we provide referrals to appropriate external counselling, occupational health, or disability support services.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Alumni Network -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">After Your Doctorate</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Alumni Network</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Completion is not the end of your relationship with Brenkley Doctoral College. Our alumni community keeps you connected to the research conversations, the people, and the institution that shaped your doctorate.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Brenkley Doctoral College alumni span the UK and beyond, working in senior leadership, policy, education, healthcare, and management consulting. The alumni network provides informal mentoring, research collaboration opportunities, and a community of peers who understand the practitioner-scholar experience.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Alumni receive ongoing access to the Brenkley Doctoral College online library, invitations to all Brenkley Doctoral College events (including the Annual Symposium), and opportunities to contribute to the development of future researchers as mentors, guest speakers, or external examiners.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Lifelong Library Access</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Alumni retain access to the Brenkley Doctoral College digital library and database subscriptions for three years post-completion, with annual renewal options thereafter.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Alumni Events</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Dedicated alumni sessions at the Annual Symposium, plus occasional alumni-only research and networking events throughout the year.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Publication Support</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Support for turning your thesis into journal articles, book chapters, or practitioner publications — including editorial guidance from Brenkley Doctoral College faculty.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Experience it for yourself</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The best way to understand the Brenkley Doctoral College experience is to speak with us and with our researchers. Arrange a conversation with our team, or attend one of our open events.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Start your application</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
